# Pro Components Law: Business Views, ProTable, ProForm

Applies to all **business views** (CRUD, dashboards) and usage of the **ProTable** and **ProForm** engine components. Violations are architecture regressions.

---

## LAW 1 — PrimeVue Purity (The Iron Law)

All tabular data and user input **MUST** use PrimeVue components. Native HTML elements are FORBIDDEN.

```html
<!-- ❌ FORBIDDEN -->
<table><tr><td>Name</td></tr></table>
<form @submit.prevent="onSubmit">
  <input type="text" v-model="name" />
  <select v-model="status">...</select>
</form>

<!-- ✅ REQUIRED -->
<ProTable :columns="columns" :data="rows" :loading="loading" />
<ProForm :schema="schema" @submit="onSubmit" />
```

**Allowed native HTML in views:** `<div>`, `<section>`, `<span>`, `<p>`, `<h1>`–`<h6>` — structural containers only.

**NEVER use:** `<table>`, `<tr>`, `<td>`, `<th>`, `<thead>`, `<tbody>`, `<form>`, `<input>`, `<select>`, `<textarea>`, `<button>` (use PrimeVue `<Button>` instead).

---

## LAW 1.5 — Custom Wrapper Selection Matrix

When a Pro wrapper exists, direct raw component usage is rejected by default.

| Raw / Legacy usage | Required wrapper / API |
|---|---|
| `<DataTable>` + `<Column>` | `<ProTable>` |
| Multi-field `<form>` (2+ fields) | `<ProForm :schema>` |
| `<Dialog>` / `<Drawer>` for business flows | `useDialog().openDialog()` / `useDialog().confirm*()` |

---

## LAW 1.6 — Intent -> Wrapper Quick Mapping

| Intent | MUST Use |
|---|---|
| CRUD / Server table / Infinite / Virtual list | `<ProTable>` |
| Create / Edit / Validation / DAG form | `<ProForm>` |
| Confirm / Delete confirm / Info prompt | `useDialog` |

---

## LAW 1.7 — Hard Reject Examples

```vue
<!-- ❌ FORBIDDEN -->
<DataTable :value="rows"><Column field="name" header="Name" /></DataTable>
<Dialog v-model:visible="visible" />
<form><InputText v-model="form.name" /><Select v-model="form.type" /></form>

<!-- ✅ REQUIRED -->
<ProTable :columns="columns" :data="rows" />
<!-- useDialog().openDialog(...) / useDialog().confirm(...) -->
<ProForm :schema="schema" @submit="onSubmit" />
```

