## LAW 2 — Business View Structure

Admin table, form, settings, and CRUD views **MUST** keep actions and content in a clear,
task-driven structure. Read-heavy detail or inspection views may use a split master/detail layout
when that structure matches the page's primary task. Standard CRUD, table, and form views should
keep actions in the page toolbar and content in the primary flow.

### 2.1 — Root Wrapper

```html
<!-- ✅ REQUIRED: transparent root — Transparent Root Policy -->
<!-- ❌ FORBIDDEN: any bg-* / surface-* / material-* on root wrapper -->
<div class="col-stretch gap-md">
  <div class="layout-narrow col-stretch gap-md">
    <!-- content sections below -->
  </div>
</div>
```

**[LAW] View Root Wrappers:**
- For standard flowing content (for example showcases, forms), the root wrapper MUST NOT constrain height. Use `col-stretch gap-md` or `layout-container` (for examples).
- Do NOT wrap the entire view in `<CScrollbar>` if the parent `LayoutAdmin` already provides the main scrollable area.
- Use `<CScrollbar>` only for local scrollable regions (for example inside a fixed-height sidebar, drawer panel, or a specific datatable wrapper).
- Detail or inspection layouts are appropriate only when the page's primary task is readonly inspection, profile detail, or document review.

### 2.2 — Scrollable Container

**MANDATORY:** All scrollable regions MUST use `<CScrollbar>`. NEVER use `overflow-auto`.

```html
<!-- ❌ FORBIDDEN -->
<div class="overflow-auto h-full">...</div>

<!-- ✅ REQUIRED -->
<CScrollbar class="col-fill">...</CScrollbar>
```

### 2.3 — Content Sections

Use `material-elevated` for each logical content section (search area, table area, detail card). Sections are separated by `gap-md` or `gap-lg` on the `layout-narrow` wrapper.

```html
<!-- ✅ Two-section view: search panel + table panel -->
<div class="layout-narrow col-stretch gap-md">
  <section class="material-elevated col-stretch gap-sm">
    <!-- search form / filters -->
  </section>

  <section class="material-elevated col-stretch">
    <!-- ProTable -->
  </section>
</div>
```

`material-elevated` = `bg-card text-card-foreground rounded-lg p-md border border-solid border-transparent dark:border-border/15 shadow-sm hover:shadow-md transition-all duration-md`

**FORBIDDEN on sections:**
- ❌ `padding: 16px` inline — use `p-md`
- ❌ `background: #fff` — use `bg-card`
- ❌ `width: 800px` — use `w-full`, `layout-narrow`, `col-fill`
- ❌ `text-gray-700`, `bg-white`, raw Tailwind colors

