## LAW 4 — ProForm Usage

### 4.1 — Always Schema-Driven

All forms with ≥2 fields **MUST** use `<ProForm>` with a typed `FormSchema`.

Internal implementation note: native `<form>` is allowed inside `packages/vue-ui/src/ProForm/**`
because it is the component boundary that provides the approved business form abstraction.
This exception must not be copied into `src/views/**`.

### 4.2 — Responsive Grid via `span` (NOT UnoCSS grid)
ProForm uses an internal 12-column CSS grid. Control layout with field `span`.

### 4.3 — Schema File Rule
Forms with **>4 fields** MUST define schema in a separate file.

